This paper deals with the development of intelligent assistants that combine task-oriented and non-task-oriented spoken dialogue systems. This topic falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and specifically spoken dialogue systems. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms to improve the performance of the system, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of log data and web search queries also involves data mining and information retrieval, which are covered under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). The paper also involves the evaluation of the system's performance, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
